    <h2>Finished my portfolio</h2>
    <p>Like most designers, I kept postponing the creation of my portfolio, seeing it as a purely transactional task, something needed only for job hunting.</p>
    <div class="paragraph-with-list-block">
      <p>Turned out, the process itself had value:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>I took a clear-eyed look at my past experience and projects with the perspective of time.</li>
        <li>I analyzed my strengths and clarified what I truly want to focus on in the future.</li>
        <li>I honed my visual skills and storytelling while crafting case studies.</li>
        <li>I captured my achievements in a tangible form — something to revisit during moments of doubt.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>It took me a long time, but I’m happy with the result. Now, instead of overexplaining what I do, I can just share a link.</p>
    </div>
